NOTES ON SERVICE REQUIREMENTS:

1. SERVICE ON DEFENDANT: MCR 2.107 governs service of papers on parties. You may serve by mail (MCR 2.107(C)(3)), personal delivery (MCR 2.107(C)(1)), or email if consented to (MCR 2.107(C)(4)).

2. SERVICE ON CHIEF JUDGE: File with Court Clerk, who will route to Chief Judge's chambers. You may also directly deliver to Chief Judge's clerk.

3. NOTICE TO JUDGE MCNEILL: While Judge McNeill will not decide the motion, courtesy requires providing notice. Deliver through Court Clerk.

4. CERTIFIED MAIL RECOMMENDED: For important motions like disqualification, certified mail with return receipt is strongly recommended for proof of service.

5. TIMING: Serve as soon as possible after filing. MCR 2.107(C)(3) requires service "promptly" after filing.

6. PROOF: Keep all proof of service (receipts, tracking numbers, etc.) in your case file.

